textAfterTable: 38 Songs Biography Born: 09 November 1963 in Milan, Italy Genre: Pop Years Active: '80s, '90s, '00s, '10s Romantic balladeer Biagio Antonacci emerged from the Milan area in the late '80s and gradually became one of the most successful Italian pop singers of the modern era. Born in Milan on November 9, 1963, Antonacci was raised in Rozzano. While studying geometry, in 1988 he entered the annual Festival di Sanremo with his song "Voglio Vivere in un Attimo," scoring a recording contract immediately thereafter.
